cked up for processing until writing is complete.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Correctness depends on live write-in-progress timing and filesystem behavior (REAL-INFRA). Mocked completion checks can pass while real partial-read races fail (MOCK-HIDE).","test_description":"Start daemon, begin writing a large file in chunks from a separate process/thread, trigger arrival event naturally, and verify no processing starts until writer closes/completes; then assert one successful final processing pass.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.79,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
